xy' + y = 0,\quad y(4) = 6
\frac{y'}{y} = \frac{-1}{x} = \int \frac{y'}{y} dx = \int \frac{-1}{x} dx = \int \frac{1}{y} dy = -\int \frac{1}{x} dx = ln(y) = -ln(x) +  c
24/x
24/x
\ln y+\ln x=c \\ \ln xy=c \\ y(4)=6 \implies c=\ln 24 \\ \ln xy=\ln 24 \\ xy=24
\ln y=-\ln x +C
y=e^C x^{-1}
x=4
y=6
e^C=24
